</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,970,1642]" box="[197,1262,1402,1427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1403,1427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
Preliminarily, this species was wrongly named as 
<taxonomicName box="[878,968,1403,1427]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aculops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[878,968,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Aculops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<emphasis box="[1023,1059,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">cfr.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hinz" box="[1065,1250,1402,1427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Hinz ̓ H · L · ̓ Gerber ̓ E · ̓ Cristοfarο ̓ Μ · ̓ Τrοnci ̓ C · ̓ Seier ̓ Μ · ̓ Κοrοtyaev ̓ Β · A · ̓ Gu 1 tek 1 n ̓ L · ̓ Wi 11 iams ̓ L · &amp; Schwarz 1 ander ̓ M. (2008) All against one: first results of a newly formed foreign exploration consortium for the biological control of perennial pepperweed. Proceedings of the XII International Symposium of Biological Control of Weeds, La Grande Motte, France, 22 - 27 April, 2007. CAB International, Wallingford, UK, 154 - 159." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hinz 
<emphasis box="[1126,1183,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1189,1250,1402,1426]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,970,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,463,1438,1463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
No eriophyoids were previously known from 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1235,1438,1462]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis box="[1009,1235,1438,1462]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Lepidium latifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while 
<taxonomicName authority="Carmona 1969" authorityName="Carmona" authorityYear="1969" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Metaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapistri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Metaculus rapistri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Carmona" box="[244,413,1474,1498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Carmona, M. M. (1969) Metaculus rapistri n. sp. (Acarina: Eriophyoidea) from Portugal. Agronomia Lusitana, 30, 89 - 92 + 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1969">
Carmona 
<number box="[357,413,1474,1498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[625,849,1476,1499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Rapistrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rugosum">
<emphasis box="[625,849,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Rapistrum rugosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) All. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1312,1436,1476,1499]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Metaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapistri">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">M. rapistri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the prodorsal shield pattern, thinner anterior lobe, higher number of dorsal semiannuli, less number of striae on the female coverflap. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[620,767,1547,1571]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Metaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidifolii">
<emphasis box="[620,767,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">M. lepidifolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Keifer 1962" authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1962" box="[1091,1436,1546,1571]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Metaculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syzygii">
<emphasis box="[1091,1292,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Metaculus syzygii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Keifer" box="[1300,1436,1546,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Keifer, H. H. (1962) Eriophyid Studies B - 6. Bureau of Entomology, California Department of Agriculture, 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1962">
Keifer 
<number box="[1380,1436,1546,1570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs mainly by the length of the median line, appearance of the admedian lines, length of the 
<emphasis box="[1412,1435,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">sc</emphasis>
setae, and ventral distribution of microtubercles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
